Our Disclosure of Your Information
We will not use your personal information for any purpose other than to complete a transaction with you.
We do not rent, sell or share your personal information and we will not disclose any of your personally identifiable information to third parties unless:
we have your permission
to provide products or services you've requested
to help investigate, prevent or take action regarding unlawful and illegal activities, suspected fraud, potential threat to the safety or security of any person, violations of BrandsForLess.com terms of use or to defend against legal claims
special circumstances such as compliance with subpoenas, court orders, requests/order from legal authorities or law enforcement agencies requiring such disclosure
What choices are available to you regarding Collection, Use and Distribution of Your Information?
Supplying personally identifiable information is entirely voluntary. You are not required to register with us in order to browse our Site. However, we offer some services only to visitors who do register.
You may change your interests at any time and may opt-in or opt-out of any marketing / promotional / newsletters mailings. BrandsForLess.com reserves the right to send you certain service related communication, considered to be a part of your BrandsForLess.com account without offering you the facility to opt-out. You may update your information and change your account settings at any time. Please use the contact information provided below for the above purposes.
Upon request, we will remove / block your personally identifiable information from our database, thereby canceling your registration. However, your information may remain stored in archive on our servers even after the deletion or the termination of your account.
If we plan to use your personally identifiable information for any commercial purposes, we will notify you at the time we collect that information and allow you to opt-out of having your information used for those purposes.
How to unsubscribe from our Newsletter?
You may unsubscribe from our newsletters by clicking on 'unsubscribe' link located at the bottom of each newsletter.
Security
To protect against the loss, misuse and alteration of the information under our control, we have in place appropriate physical, electronic and managerial procedures. For example, our servers are accessible only to authorized personnel and that your information is shared with respective personnel on need to know basis to complete the transaction and to provide the services requested by you.
Although we will endeavor to safeguard the confidentiality of your personally identifiable information, transmissions made by means of the Internet cannot be made absolutely secure. By using this Site, you agree that we will have no liability for disclosure of your information due to errors in transmission or unauthorized acts of third parties.
Access or change your personally identifiable information
To protect your privacy and security, we will verify your identity before granting access or making changes to your personally-identifying information. If you have registered your profile on Brands For Less, your BrandsForLess.com User ID and Password are required in order to access your profile information.
We reserve the right to change or update our policies at any time. Such changes shall be effective immediately upon posting to this Site. You can offer your views, suggestions, if any, by submitting your feedback using the form in the Contact Us section.
Data Security
This Privacy Policy explains how Brands For Less, the operator of the Brands For Less application, collects, processes, and uses personal data for specified purposes and to a defined extent.
We treat all personal data processed through the use of the Brands For Less application confidentially and in compliance with applicable data protection regulations.
By downloading the application, you acknowledge and agree to the data collection, processing, and usage procedures outlined in detail below.
Data Processing During Download and Installation of the Application
To facilitate the purchase and installation of our application and to provide you with the content, you may need to enter into a usage agreement with a third-party provider. During the download, necessary information, including your username, email address, customer number or account, payment information, download time, and individual device identification number, is transferred to the respective App Store or Play Store. We do not control this data collection and are not responsible for it. We process this data only to facilitate the download of the application to your mobile device. Additional information can be found in the privacy policy of the third-party provider.
Data Processing by Brands For Less
Any personal data collected through your use of the Brands For Less application will be utilized solely for operating the application, communication, and direct marketing related to our products and events.
Certain data transmitted by your browser to our server is automatically collected for displaying the application and ensuring its stability and security. This data includes:
Type and unique ID of your mobile device
IP address
Date and time of server request
Referrer URL
Access status/HTTP status code
Amount of data transmitted
Type of mobile operating system
Language and version of mobile browser software
Diagnostic data
Upon installing the application, certain system queries may occur on your mobile device, depending on the services used within the application, such as:
Device ID
Location
Push ID received during push registration
You can provide and revoke consent to release your mobile device location data at any time for receiving local offers after app installation.
We utilize beacon technology when you are near our stores or inside them. Beacons are transmitters based on Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) technology that send signals to receivers, such as mobile devices, identifying the beacon when in proximity.
We will not track your location without your consent. Your mobile device will request permission before using a location-based content or service within the app. If permission is denied, we will not process any location-based content data. We won't store your location data permanently, only as long and as necessary to process the location-based content or service request. You can withdraw consent for location-based information collection in your device settings at any time.
The information in your user profile is used solely to tailor the app's offerings to your interests and needs and is entirely voluntary.
Use of Collected Data during Registration
During registration under our terms of use, we will request the following data through our input form:
Salutation, first name, last name
Address
Date of Birth
Email address
Preferred stores
These data inquiries are essential to provide our services under our terms of use.
The data will be stored as long as your registration is valid. Legal storage obligations, such as those stipulated by commercial or tax laws, will remain unaffected.
When using external service providers for personal data processing, we ensure careful selection, written commissioning, and compliance with our instructions. The service providers will not share this data with third parties and will delete it after completing the contract and complying with statutory storage periods unless consent to store it beyond this has been granted.
Your registration details are saved in your account and on the servers.
In addition, certain data may be stored on your mobile device.
Disclosure to Third Parties
We will only share your personal data with other parties, including companies and external individuals, if legal permission to do so exists.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies. We utilize cookies and similar technologies within the application to enhance user experience and overall efficiency. Cookies are small text files assigned to your browser and stored on your hard drive, enhancing the app's user-friendliness and effectiveness.
Cookies can contain data allowing device recognition but typically don't personally identify users. We differentiate between session cookies (deleted after closing the browser) and permanent cookies (stored beyond the session).
We use necessary cookies for app navigation, basic functions, and security purposes. Consent-based technologies that enhance app usage may also be utilized.
Analysis Services
We utilize beaconsmind AG to provide insights into app usage, user preferences, statistical analyses of products and stores, and purchase histories. The statistics obtained help us enhance the app's offerings and make them more appealing to users. In addition, with your consent, we can track your presence in a store using the beacon technology mentioned.
Google Analytics
We utilize features of Google Analytics. Google Analytics helps us analyze and enhance app usage regularly, utilizing obtained statistics to improve offerings for users.
Sentry
Our app uses the error diagnosis service Sentry, provided by Functional Software, Inc., to diagnose app crashes or unexpected errors. Relevant information is sent to Sentry's servers for analysis and diagnostics.
Your Rights
You have specific rights concerning your personal data under applicable laws:
Right to information
Right to rectification or erasure
Right to restriction of processing
Right to object to processing
Right to data portability
